                    <span>The building of the transcontinental railroad was one of our greatest achievements. Ambrose is able to put us in the time period, where 500 barrels of blasting powder are used per day to blast the way through mountains to make tunnels for the railroad.  Chinese are the ones to do the blasting as white folks are too scared to do it.
<br />The advent of dynamite adds a new dimension, with it much greater power, and it's unpredictibality as to when it will explode.  
<br />Finding out that Lincoln was a railroad fan was interesting. 
<br />The idea that they had to do all this without bulldozers, cranes, etc. I found facinating.  The ability to lay over a mile a day, 6 miles in one day, by hand is amazing. 
<br /> It takes years here in Atlanta to get a single overpass completed. 
<br />
<br />The stories of the financial theivery are interesting, by the rail barons and congressmen. 
